  "details": "The gnutls package provide the GNU Transport Layer Security (GnuTLS) library, which implements cryptographic algorithms and protocols such as SSL, TLS, and DTLS.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* gnutls: vulnerable to Minerva side-channel information leak (CVE-2024-28834)\n* gnutls: potential crash during chain building/verification (CVE-2024-28835)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
